<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-11T15:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-11T15:45:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 715.1715/66</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-11T15:00:00-05:45">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Nicaraguan Minister at Washington has been appointed Nicaraguan
                                representative in Nicaraguan-Honduran boundary question, and Adolfo
                                Cardenas of Managua will be sent in the capacity of engineer and
                                secretary.</p>
                            <p>Copy sent to American Legation Tegucigalpa.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>